    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="481"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <head>481. Memorandum From the Assistant Secretary of State for Near Eastern, South
                    Asian, and African Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_AGV1" type="from"
                        >Allen</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d481fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 784A.5622/7–2056. Top Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BDC1"
                            >Bergus</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">Burdett</persName>;
                        initialed by <persName corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> for <persName
                            corresp="#p_AGV1">Allen</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Canadian F–86 Aircraft for Israel; “Operation Stockpile”</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Discussion:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> has reported (Tab
                        B)<note n="2" xml:id="d481fn2">Tab B is printed <ref target="#d480">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> that the points we instructed him to make to the Canadian
                    Foreign Minister (Tab C)<note n="3" xml:id="d481fn3">Tab C is <ref
                            target="#d471">Document 471</ref>.</note> have had considerable effect.
                    Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> recommends: 1) Communicate
                    to the Canadians the general content of the statement to be made on “Operation
                    Stockpile”; 2) Approve and announce the issuance of export licenses for at least
                    some helicopters, machine guns, and scout cars for Israel; 3) Take some action
                    to satisfy Canadian requirements for Western consultation on this matter— either
                    through the Ambassadorial committee in Washington or private talks with a
                    Canadian emissary in Washington.</p>
                <p>We believe we should move forward with the Canadians and with the Stockpile
                    announcement.</p>
                <pb facs="0904" n="876" xml:id="pg_876"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Recommendations:</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>That you sign the attached telegrams to Ottawa (Tab A).<note n="4"
                            xml:id="d481fn4">Not attached to the source text. Presumably telegrams
                            33 and 34, <ref target="#d482">
                                <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>
                            </ref> and <ref target="#d483">Document 483</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>That, subject to Canadian acceptance of our course of action, <gloss
                            target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss> be authorized to proceed with the quiet and
                        piecemeal release to Israel of 5 helicopters, 400 machine guns, and 130
                            <persName corresp="#p_WGTD1">White</persName> Scout Cars
                        (half-tracks).</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>That, provided there is nothing in <persName corresp="#p_HD1"
                            >Hammarskjold</persName>’s report regarding his trip to the Near East
                        which would militate against such action, we proceed with preparations to
                        make the announcement of “Operation Stockpile” about August 1.<note n="5"
                            xml:id="d481fn5">A note at the bottom of the source text reads: “See
                            Eyes Only telegram 33 to Ottawa.”</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
